            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>This collection primarily contains correspondence between Ulysses G. Grant and William Elrod, the manager of Grant&#039;s farm in St. Louis County, Mo., where his father-in-law, Frederick F. Dent, lived. The collection also includes an insurance policy for $2,000, taken out by Grant on the farmhouse occupied by Elrod; state and county property tax receipts (1871-73) describing the location of the farm; various newspaper clippings; and a photograph of Grant. The correspondence is published in <emph render="italic">The Papers of Ulysses S. Grant</emph>, ed. John Y. Simon.</p>
                                 <p>The Survey acquired the collection in 1940.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


